text:
If you physically dissect along Torrent-Guasp’s cleavage plane and unfold the ventricular myocardium, what you get is basically: MÖBIUS-LISTING which is a long, almost rectangular muscular strip with a central 180° fold if you re-wrap it, connecting basal and apical loops.

So the heart is a particular Generalized Möbius–Listing body, with the unfolded strip realized as a planar rectangular patch and the folded configuration given by the GML embedding in 3D.

@cube_flipper @algekalipso you probably know this already, but I wanted to share that each time I see I can't stop thinking at it as a proton/photon synchrotron that channels prana into and from higher dimensions.

